caption: I was pretty disappointed by the pupusas and the cod tacos. The ingredients tasted great, but the food just didn't look appetizing and the portion size of the pupusas are upsettingly small. I'd have to check out some of their other items, but I highly doubt I'll be returning any time soon, maybe they need a Salvadoreño chef.
Really nice Latin inspired cocktail bar with amazing drinks. All focused on agave based spirits and other flavours and aromas from Latin America. Cool vibe and friendly staff.
Food was nice but it’s over priced for what it is.
Amazing drinks as always, the food is surprisingly great every time they change menus

Wheres the sixth star button?! What a refreshing experiance even during the pandemic! We braved 28 degree weather and it was well worth it! Open air but heating keeps it as comfortable as possible! The cod tacos were light and airy and deliciously tart with capers and pickled onions....no tartar needed. Pupusas were great too!  Brilliant. All in all well balanced portions and delicious flavor! Coming back again soon!

It was freezing out, and it was still completely worth it. Yummy enchiladas en mole, and cocktails. The spiked hot chocolate and churros was the perfect way to close. Service was kind and patient, in spite of the challenges and limitations COVID-19 brings. And they take all precautions very seriously which made me feel safe. Can't wait to go back when its just not below 30F and windy.
Amazing place with delicious mexican cookies.Now i have to take the food and eat it somwhere else the quality has not changed.
Christmas cocktails and Mexican food how can you go wrong!
Amazing cocktails. Great food

We had an amazing time in the back garden at Leyenda the other night. Tasty and inventive cocktails and small bites. The backyard was well spaced out and the staff were very attentive and following precautions. Highly recommend for your next date or gathering.
They need better workers and not rude.But the foods here good.

Had the most delicious brunch this past Sunday, you need to check them out. Cocktails unique and delicious, chicken mole/fish tacos the best in the neighborhood!  I can't wait to go back and try some of the other amazing dishes! The service was excellent too, friendly, attentive but not too much, just right! Thank you Leyenda for making our day!
Been going to this bar for years! Consistent top tier service. Amazing cocktails and amazing food.
Amazing cocktails, delicious Mexican dishes and a beautiful patio out back. What's not to love?
Favorite spot on Smith Street. Great staff, Incredible drinks and yum food.
Great bar! Amazing service, and cocktails! 🙌🏼❤️✨
Awesome Latin American/Carribean inspired cocktails + decent food. A spot I now frequent visit!
Great service, attentive, courteous, food on point and great drinks!!
Plates and utensils came with stains on them and we mentioned it and got a replacement of more stained plates and utensils.
Excellent, different cocktails. Definitely to try
Great ambience, tasty drinks, and pleasant staff. Going to go back to try the food next time.
Leyanda’s food is only overshadowed by their incredible cocktails. A previous James Beard finalist, this cocktail bar is just amazing. Great music, talented bartenders.
Solid Latin food (including options for vegetarians and pescetarians). Enjoyed the panuchos and pupusas.  Sadly didn't try the cocktails this time around!
Really great cocktails!
Excellent food, drinks were great and atmosphere is wonderful
Great bar! Good vibes! Arturo, behind the bar made our night. What a gem! He was a great bartender and made us feel so welcome!! Will definitely return back! Highly recommend!
Was there last night, Monday night. The place was full and vibe was great. Had few drinks and ate. Really had a great time, the service, people and the place is very good. Definitely will be coming.
One of my favourite places in New York City! A Brooklyn gem with amazing cocktails and fantastic food. If in NYC or Brooklyn make sure you get to Layenda.
Our go to spot in the neighborhood! Always a good vibe, fairly busy but we’ve never really had to wait to get a table. The panuchos is our favorite dish!
My fav to go too spot! Tacos are a hit
Food and cocktails are sooooo good. I loved the vibe here! I tried a couple of cocktails and Room with View is FIVE stars!👍
Excellent cocktails and a very good brunch to pair with it.  Chilaquiles are delicious, try pairing them with the Brooklyn Burro.  Will be back soon for a nighttime visit.
Really nice well balanced creative cocktails. Tasty nibbles. Great date spot. Go early, can get crowded.

Turned up at 5pm on a Monday specifically for the long advertised happy hour, to find out they weren't currently offering it, I'd checked before heading out and could not find any notice otherwise. Service felt cold, which is a great shame as the cocktails themselves are excellent.
Service was great, food was good, drinks were ok
Great staff, wonderful cocktails
love the food and drinks and staff, not crazy about the high chair tables.

Holy Moly. They have such a good Mezcal top shelf that already puts them into a different category, but Leyenda has the other 5-stars stuff, too...: Great food, the nicest staff, and a serious cocktail.
Check out the snow globe in the back!
Loved Leyenda - great vibe, good food & cocktails...The Christmas  Cosmo was amazing! My husband loved the Tia Mia. The chicken tacos &the croquettes were great.
Awesome drinks and food, great looking spot
Really delicious cocktails. Cozy atmosphere. They have small plates.
Great, cozy place with good festive drinks. Tried the croquettas with manchego cheese and it was delicious. The flan was okay.

They are awesome. It's super festive, the food was delicious, the drinks were awesome, and the service was amazing. We had a group of 10 and the servers were so great. Would give more stars if I could!
Romantic latin bar, exotic and cozy in Carroll Garden, Brooklyn area.
Food was great. Their skirt steak was cooked to perfection!!
One of the best bars in the neighborhood
Amazing cocktail menu and super attentive staff. Would deff come back
Delicious creative drinks. The menu is like Latin tapas. They have a fair amount of gluten free options. It’s a fun environment.

Service was pretty awful and it was very crowded. We sat in the back and this large group of people keep banging into the back of our booth. The back of the booth was so wobbly that I was so annoyed and uncomfortable leaning back that I just learned forward my entire meal. Not too relaxing. We also had over four servers so we didn't know who to tip. Also, no one asked if we wanted refills or needed anything was our food was served. Food was good though. A+ to the chefs.
Great artisan cocktails
Cozy. Fantastic bites & drinks!
Very inventive cocktails! Great Tiki drinks and some very tasty mezcal cocktails, as well.

World famous cocktail menu and some of the best food in the city. GREAT spot for a date night, drinks /nibbles with colleagues, friends or family. Gets busy due to popularity but if you time it right you’ll get a table to call your own for the evening.
Tasty tacos and well-crafted drinks!
Great drinks decent food, awesome atmosphere. The menu is always changing here to make room for new and interesting cocktails, made fresh by some super nice bartenders. Great date spot too.
Drinks are amazing, atmosphere is warm and inviting, friendly staff.
I love this place it's very friendly enjoying the Food and Drinks
Excellent dark bar, great cocktails and conversation level noise.
Everything was awesome. Great experience, I would definitely go back!

Good god did this place hit the nail on the head with everything. I've never had a place at a 10/10 level on all three areas I really focus on when evaluating my experience at a restaurant... food, cocktails/drinks, and ambiance. If you appreciate a great cocktail program, perfectly executed Latin bar food, in a little unassuming spot already crowded with bars and places on the "best of" lists, you need to try Leyenda as soon as humanly possible.

The cocktails are good and creative. The ambiance is nice. The food is hit or miss. The "ceviche" was awful. It had apples in it and what appeared to be heavy cream. Whatever it was, "ceviche" should not have been in the name. The waitress was attentive and friendly, the staff was friendly. The drinks are not strong. The place was kind of pretentious in that it is basically all about ambiance and presentation. While it wasn't an awful experience I can't see going there again.

The food and the drinks were absolutely top quality between the taste and the execution. But the prices were high for the portion size.  The atmosphere was quiet on a Tuesday night. Not sure if the experience is different other days of the week.

Chic joint offering mexican/central american inspired cuisine and some serious cocktails. Walked in here around 8pm on a sunday evening and were able to get a seat in the cute little back patio without having to wait. Not much in way of a view but it was nice to sit outdoors. They also have a couple of seats at the windows facing Smith St along with the regular inside seating.  Started off with a couple of cocktails since that seems to be one of the USPs of Leyenda. Got the Grass Roots Persuasion and another one served in a skull shaped container, the name of which I cannot recall. Both were well presented and tasted phenomenal. They run a little pricey but are solid for the $. For food decided to get the house made guac, fava bean empanadas and the pupusas. Guac was great, served in an avocado skin and came with fresh chips and salsa. The empanadas were delicious as were the pupusas. Full marks for presentation on everything - drinks and food. They really do put effort into it which reflects in the dining experience. My only quip was that the portion sizes were rather small although we did only order what would traditionally be considered appetizers. A few more vegetarian items on the entrées would have been great. Service was on the slower side but friendly regardless. Will be back again for their cocktails and to check out their brunch.
This place has excellent cocktails. Extended list of mezcal and tequila. The food is also great.

This place is AWESOME. I hosted a birthday party there and had such an incredible experience. The staff was so extremely accommodating from planning beforehand through to the end of the evening! I hosted about 20 people who were all so impressed with the service, food (slash drinks), and space! I cannot recommend this place enough!!

Love everything about this place. The vibe, the decor, the food, the staff and the damn good cocktails they serve! I ddn’t know about the place so I tried a classic, and hands down, the best mojito I’v ever tasted! I thought I knew what mojito should taste like, until I had theirs! we happened to be there during the 4th year anniversary so the place was packed and the special classics available for cheap! Their cocktails are inventive, fresh and well balanced -it was too dangerous we couldn’t stop drinking. Every cocktail that we drank was concocted with attention down to every detail, even the little garnishes that come with it! Great place!
Great guac and good happy hour drinks
Very flavorful. Pupisas, vegan tacos, skirt steak and tostones all good

Everyone who worked at Leyenda was friendly and accommodating. My girlfriend and I came from the airport with all of our luggage and they found a place for us to set it so we could relax and enjoy our time here. The staff was very attentive as well. We will definitely be coming back on future trips to Brooklyn!
Best cocktail in town.
Good drinks
Delicious drinks and lovely atmosphere. Would highly recommend!
Love the late happy hour ! Start by 11 pm if I’m not wrong. Everything in the drinks menu were so great!!!!!!!! The bartender was so friendly!!  Love everything from this place!!!!!!!!!

Been dying to come here ever since we went to Machete's in Barcelona and they recommended we check it out when we got back to Brooklyn. Great cocktails, friendly staff and the food was amazing. If you are near by you must stop in cant wait to get back soon.
Good food, great patio. Haven't had their cocktails yet, but I've heard great things.

Can't recommend it enough. Fantastic drinks (Semifinalist for the JBF Outstanding Bar Program!), yummy snacks, excellent service, great vibes. Not super high-energy, but it's not gonna put you to sleep either. Just a killer bar all around—especially if you like mezcal and tequila. If you're in the neighborhood, don't miss it!
It's even better everytime I come back.
Great drinks and decor!
Some of the best cocktails I've had in Brooklyn. Nice happy hour menu, fun appetizers, quality drink experiences from a professional, personable bar staff. Go early to grab a seat!
Fantastic cocktails in a beautiful spot.
Incredible drinks, awesome service, delicious food. I come here every time I’m in town.
I stepped out of Brooklyn when I walked in!  Beautiful experience!

Leyenda had incredible cocktails, great food (I want to go back just to try the entire menu), and great team work service. The restaurant was very loud, but it won't stop us from visiting again. We will definitely be back.

The name means legend, and it's very religiously themed. Not sure if that's some hipster irony I just couldn't connect, but regardless I loved this place. Great communal environment for friends grabbing drinks and a brunch. Service was a little slow at times, but in fairness, I was member to a large party. Drinks were all good (I tried about 5 different cocktails). The steak with chimichurri was a great bite and perfectly cooked to order.

Leyenda is a bar run by arguably one of the biggest names in the industry Ivy Mix and she did an AMAZING job with this spot! Latin inspired cocktails and a Cachaca selection that will rival any other spot in BK.  We had the pleasure of having Emily as our server and she could not have been nicer and more knowledgeable about the menu. She recommended some awesome cocktails on the menu and even gave us an “off menu” option which, as a bartender myself, know that that means it’s a solid drink and it absolutely was! She even came to us with a couple Mezcal shots as a thank you for being great guests which was an amazing way to end an amazing experience at Leyenda, a place that I will go back to again and again!
White people taco place. Great tiny flavor
What a revelation! I think this used to be a pizza joint!? Whatever! Now it’s like an upscale Mexican tiki bar or something. Great cocktail selection, wonderful servers (and owners) and great snacks.

The cocktails almost save this place, but the service and food make it a must miss. If you sit at the bar it’s alright, but if you take a table on the patio you can expect to be ignored through most of the night. The Mexican food was also really bland and forgettable.
Great Place. Very detailed decoration and awesome drinks.
Great signature cocktails! Bartenders are Milk and Honey worthy. The Food is incredible!

Always a great spot for cocktails but it's also very good for food. We went during the sleigenda (holiday) time which was cute. Their brunch is solid and never packed. The torta sandwich is the way to go and big enough to split if you want to try other things.
Great drinking snacks. Not consistent though.
(Translated by Google) Good place to have a cocktail or an informal dinner  (Original) Buen lugar para tomar un cóctel o una cena informal

The atmosphere was exactly what I was in the mood for. A dimmed, cozy, and conversation friendly bar. The staff was friendly and the drinks were tasty. We did not order any food aside from the home made chips and guac, which paired well with the rum punch.

We enjoyed the tacos Al Pastor and a couple of their fancy drinks. The Date night was delicious and perfectly balanced, not too sweet. The chiller instinct was a strong, tasty, yet classy bourbon drink.
Love Leyenda! The cocktails are excellent, as you'd expect from the owners of brilliant Clover Club.
Great place, especially if you eat before you go.  Plates aren't that small, but portions are.  Had to order 8 between two of us.
Great Mezcal cocktail selection for all taste palates. Didn't try the food but the menu is definitely why I'll return! Staff is friendly, knowledge and the service is very quick!

Cocktails and food were great. My only knock is that the busser quickly swiped my plate from me with one enchilada still on it. When I informed him I wasn't finished his response was "oh i'm sorry it just looked like a plate of mush."  Not a great way to describe your own food.  UPDATE: The GM has promptly reached out and I consider the issue resolved. Kudos to them!
The cocktails are A++. Seasonal selections, and amazing service. Best there is 👏👏
Amazing cocktails and enjoyable tapas.  It is very loud and a very tight fit for seating.
Superb bartenders and lively atmosphere. The drinks are unique and tasty and reasonably priced. Big fan of this spot. Make sure you try the Michelada!
Tastey drinks, and interesting south American dishes, nice and cozy atmosphere. Music felt a bit loud, but maybe I'm just getting old ,)
Amazing food
Numerous cocktail selections in Cobble Hill, Brooklyn. Great location to sit down with friends, celebrate birthdays, and lots of South American food selection.

💕 all day!

Seriously my favorite cocktail bar in NYC. They have the best happy hour specials and really really amazing cocktails. My favorites are the Spicy Paloma during happy hour or the La Sonambula. Food here is also very good.
Four stars for the drinks, one star for the food. Have been here multiple times and tried many dishes on the menu. Sad to report the food is just not very good.
Amazing cocktails and delicious food. The bartenders are skilled and friendly. Overall, the service is very attentive and welcoming. We had a great time!!
Delicious! I recommend the mole enchiladas. The cocktails are great, too -- not too sweet and very inventive!

Solid selection of cocktails, mostly tequila based. Love that the menu shows what type of glass each drink comes in. There's a patio space, as well as some nice vibes inside. Wouldn't recommend it on a super hot day, but otherwise it's worth checking out.
Cute place, nice outdoor patio
Wonderful food and great cocktails
Best cocktails in all of New York City
Great vibe! Great cocktails and great service! The food was also a very nice surprise!! Tucked in the heart of Smith St, Leyanda is a nice addition to the vibrant area!
Good mezcal selection and the cocktails were really good
Helpful staff   good food  fun drinks   li ed the kitchy decor
Fancy little bar
This place is awesome. They could use more staff (service is a bit slow) but it’s good food, great cocktails and there’s a back patio that’s awesome.

I was excited to try this place based off the reviews and was really disappointed. Best thing abt here were the churros and our waitress. All three drinks we tried were disgusting or off. They were pretty but not good.  Our chicken tacos were just ok and small. The skirt steak was a little salty. Honestly it was a sad night for our girl's night at Leyenda. Wouldn't recommend or go back.
Has good punch
Excellent cocktails, excellent small plates, expensive, worth a visit
Drinks great, food ... meh ...

Nice low key bar with excellent cocktails. The atmosphere is pretty laid back and relaxed. They have an extensive drink menu with tons of choices, guaranteed to find something you're interested in. The cocktails aren't cheap but they're worth the money.  They also have some small plates which would be good for sharing. It's cozy and welcoming, and the service is great.
One of my favorite cocktail bars in the neighborhood. Food is so-so and expensive, but drinks are amazing. Specializes in tequila and mezcal. Cool backyard when weather is nicer.
Top notch drinks and food in the Mexican/Central American tradition!
Good bar tenders and staff but food a no-go
Neighborhood bar that serves semi upscale food and drinks.  We found the tacos to be too salty and the drinks were okay.  It could have been an off night for them.
Good cocktails
It is more like a bar but the food is a bit pricey. It is worth it though because we were impressed by the quality. The cocktails also were amazing. Had a great time there.
Awesome drinks. Good food, expensive

Best latin cocktail bar in Brooklyn and even in NYC. Elegant and high quality crafted cocktails for cheap ! Food is really good too. Gets really loud on weekend nights but has an overall good vibe. I come here every weekend !!
Great bar. Great bartenders. Love the selection of spirits. The shelves are literally overflowing.
This place is so cozy and wonderful. Great fireplace, delicious cocktails, and super accommodating staff. Come early if you're hoping to snag a prime spot.
Great cocktails and food. Went again a few weeks ago and still excellent. Feel free to ask the bartenders to make you a drink.
Great drinks, food is good!
My favorite place in Brooklyn!
Great cocktails
Never had a drink here I didn't like
A little small and crowded but drinks were on point!
Service can be very slow.
Best. Best. Best cocktails in the neighborhood- friendly staff, electric vibe! Go for the holiday cocktails, you will not be disappointed!!! Oh and Garrett is the best bartender ever🙌🏻
Love Leyenda! Great spot with a nice backdoor patio  during warmer seasons. Drinks and food are magnificent! I've never had anything here that wasn't delicious.
Nice place. The brunch was very good. I had meat and eggs! The drinks were made perfect and they were extremely attentive. 10 stars
Awesome place!!! Staff was great. Exceptional cocktails, great atmosphere.  The margaritas are epic!
Really great meal and drinks here!
Met the owner and had a few drinks. All of them tasted great, the glass shape, the ice, and the liquors were all curated really well. Will definitely go again.

This place is magic. The bartenders are kind and talented and the program of drinks will thrill any cocktail nerd but is also TOTALLY available to people not so familiar. They had no problem with me ordering off menu and made me a killer drink.  The place is hip without being pretentious which is what I love. In a neighborhood that is getting very cool and at times stuffy, this is a respite and kicks ass. The clientele ranges from hipster to businessman and everyone is happy to mingle which I find to be a rarity.  GO. DRINK! Be merry.
Great brunch food and tasty drinks.

Fun place! I came here for drinks and they have a decent happy hour with good options. The food is a little on the pricy side but the food is good so worth it. I like the look of the place- has a rustic Mexican feel and the service is good. I had the hora drink- refreshing, with a kick of spice. Is a little more of a summer drink I would say cos of the fruitiness. Come here for a date, it is on the quieter side unless it fills up so is good for conversation.
Exciting cocktails
Excellent, original, exciting cocktails .. plus food is very good as well. Staff is super friendly and the place is cozy, love the outdoor in the back as well. One of the best bars on earth.
Fantastic cocktails. Cool atmosphere. Food is solid.
Great staff, fantastic food and amazing drinks. Brunch is a must!! Best brunch in the city with minimal crowds. And a Brunch happy hour (!!!) from 11-3! Easy delicious day drinking.
Really cool place, great bartenders, and Brooklyn chill.
Fancy cocktails and also great tequilas to sip. They have a nice open space at the back but it may get busy and the wait time for it can be one hour or longer. Other tables are easier to get.

I won't give it 5 stars simply because i don't expect nor do i want to see political views and opinions during my dining experience. If they can remove that i would add the extra star because the food and drinks are really tasty. Please don't alienate your customers , thats just bad for business.
Great cocktails and tapas
Stellar cocktail program, bar looks really cool. Great food and vibes in a unique room.

Great service, great tapas, and great cocktails!  I only wish they would keep their political views out of business. Unnecessary to put up a poster bashing Trump. That's  not what I expect to see when i go out.
Great drinks on a sat
Some different. Drinks was on point, food was awesome.
Unique cocktails, great food. However, the food servings are appetizer size so you need to order two if you are hungry.
Yummy yum yum yum. Had the spicy Paloma and the torta de pollo and hot diggity was it good. Chill spot, nice staff, good times. I think I shall be back.
Chillaquiles and gossip 💯
Lovely cozy spot. Great well made cocktails and tasty small plates. Josh the bartender had a great persona and the other staff were very cook.
Excellent food and Excellent service
Solid cocktails and laid back vibes

I think Leyenda, though it does have a good reputation, gets overlooked. This is one of the best bars in Brooklyn. Drinks are inventive, unique, and we'll priced. The ambiance is cool, and we've always gotten fantastic service.
Great variety of drinks and good food.
Food is absolutely delicious. Drinks are well made and strong. Service was exceptional.
Great cocktails and food

Solid cocktails, especially at happy hour prices, and good food, though a little pricey. But let's face it; if you're coming to a place like this for drinks, you may not mind dropping $16 for fancy fish tacos.

Priceless! Since you go unside, you walk into uniqueness. Friendly and great atmosphere. Feeling of a super chilled neighborhood bar with a 5 star service and experience. Amazing agave spirit collection with tasty small bites.
Solid drinks with great small plates.
Great small bites and cocktails.
Great service, helpful waiters. I had papusas and enchiladas for breakfast, and they were fine, but not memorable. I didn't try their drinks.

Outrageously good cocktails - in particular rum and mezcal/tequila based ones. The service can be a bit iffy, but that's because it's always packed. The tapas are hearty and addictive - way better than they need to be. Try the empanadas.
Best bar in the area.
Very Pricey small plates, would recommend trying the frozen margarita
Home of the best tequila/mezcal selection and best bartenders in the country.
Excellent service, very chill place to catch up with a friend, or bring a date. Food has a Latin twist, very delicious. You must try the parsley steak - never had anything like it before.
Delicious cocktails.

Very cute bar, and one of the bartenders looks like Blake Shelton if you look at him from the right angle. The cocktails were delicious, but expensive if not happy hour. There is a garden out back, but I didn't sit out there because wanted to be in the A/C.
The tiny truths about this legend are their tiny priced portions and charming garden. Lovely for small bites and chats.
Great Latino Inspired Spot! Ivy rocks...

I feel like I'm always on the hunt for a new fun place to catch up with a friend and grab drinks and bites.  Leyenda came up on the map, and it was a perfect choice. Great craft cocktails- came for happy hour. Between us, we tried probably four different ones, all were really good! Da Hora was really nice though a little fruity for me.  They sweetened my mojito no sugar order with muddled strawberries, excellent addition!!! And the shadow boxer was a great close, which might have grown a hair on my chest! Awesome combination of flavors, all making for a very enjoyable experience and an even better time ;)
Nice outdoor patio which gets early afternoon sun. Drinks aren't cheap but cocktails are great. Service could have been quicker!
A perfect match of cocktails and food - and the guacamole is particularly addictive. Plus, the brunch service, which recently started, is heaven sent. Especially if you have it the back patio.

Food was incredible. Drinks are good but pricey. Asked for a mezcal on the rocks, liked it enough that I ordered a 2nd one. Was there only with my girlfriend and our bill was over $250. Bartender didn't think to at least mention my drinks were $21 each. I feel ripped off. At least give me a heads up if I'm paying that much.
Very friendly staff and, despite the bar atmosphere, very accommodating with children.
Amazing cocktails and food.

Moved to Florida 4 months ago from California and had been looking for a new cigar spot which, as they seem, are a dime a dozen out here. I found this great local spot while searching google maps to see what shops were a little outside of my immediate area.  Needless to say this place has become my go to spot for cigars.  They have a great selection and a very good inexpensive house brand Nicaraguan cigar which I have come to really enjoy.  The owners Dan and Jody are awesome and offer complimentary coffee (this actually sold me). The shop is small and always has regulars inside when I stop in. The atmosphere is light, sports are  always on and conversation is always going. A must visit if you are into cigars and good conversation.
Unique Mexican dishes...plenty of seafood options

Service: A+++ the staff was friendly and accommodating, and the atmosphere was great.  Food: D. the only thing worth eating (and we tried about 6 of their plates plus tacos) were the flautas. Everything else tasted very generic, and was not worth the price tag.  Cocktails: A+++ these were delicious! price point was on target, and the combinations were well thought out.  tl;dr: come here for drinks at the end of the night, or before you have reservations elsewhere. don't show up hungry or you'll be disappointed.
Amazing food! The ceviche, panuchos, and empanadas will bring you back again!
